aude Reymond.  aThis first volume, published under the supervision of Jean-Daniel Candaux and Lucia Omacini, assembles the texts produced between 1774 and 1799. The volume divides into three sections: Constant's essays written when still a boy; texts stemming from his study years in Scotland, France, Switzerland and Germany; and above all his first political writings (pamphlets, speeches, articles), which appeared during the Directoire and Consulat years. Other scholars involved in the making of this volume are Simone Balayé, Mauro Barberis, Claude Bruneel, Magda Campanini, Paul Delbouille, Edouard Guitton, Kurt Kloocke, Roland Mortier and Claude Reymond.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn French.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 4aConstant. 4aFrankreich - Geschichte. 4aFrankreich - Literatur. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh1 aBalayé, Simone.1 aBarberis, Mauro.1 aBruneel, Claude.1 aCampanini, Magda.1 aCandaux, Jean-Daniel, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aCandaux, Jean-Daniel.1 aDelbouille, Paul.1 aGuitton, Edouard.1 aKloocke, Kurt.1 aMortier, Roland.1 aOmacini, Lucia, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aReymond, Claude.1 aThomson, Patrice.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Literary and Cultural Studies - 1990 - 1999z9783110637830oZDB-23-GLC0 cprintz978348450401140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311093282940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110932829423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110932829/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-GLCc1990d1999